{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015ukJaVFiuCvaw8q5jeWU8Q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14.5: Stack-Aware Verification Dockerfile Generation\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a developer verifying a Rust/Bevy project,\n    11→I want the verification Dockerfile generated with the correct toolchain and system libs,\n    12→So that verification doesn't waste time fixing container issues manually.\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→1. Given a Rust project with `bevy` in Cargo.toml dependencies, when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes: Rust toolchain via rustup, Bevy system libs (`libudev-dev`, `libasound2-dev`, `libwayland-dev`, `libxkbcommon-dev`, `libfontconfig1-dev`, `libx11-dev`), `clippy`, and `cargo-tarpaulin` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→2. Given `ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:$PATH\"` in the generated Dockerfile, when `cargo tarpaulin` is run inside the container, then it executes without requiring manual `source \"$HOME/.cargo/env\"` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→3. Given a Node.js project (package.json at root), when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes Node.js 20 LTS, npm, Semgrep, showboat, and claude-code CLI — matching current `Dockerfile.verify` functionality <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→4. Given a Python project (setup.py or pyproject.toml at root), when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes Python 3, pip, venv, Semgrep, and verification tooling <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→5. Given a Rust project WITHOUT `bevy` in Cargo.toml, when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes Rust toolchain, clippy, and cargo-tarpaulin but NOT the Bevy system libs <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→6. Given the `StackProvider` interface in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts`, when `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` is added, then all three providers (Nodejs, Python, Rust) implement the method and TypeScript compiles with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→7. Given a multi-stack project (e.g., root has both package.json and Cargo.toml), when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes tooling for ALL detected stacks <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→8. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→9. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→10. Given the 300-line NFR1 rule, when line counts are checked, then `env.ts` does not grow beyond its current 313 lines (already over limit — should shrink or stay flat by extracting the generator to a separate file) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→\n    27→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    28→\n    29→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 6): Add `getVerifyDockerfileSection(projectDir: string): string` to `StackProvider` interface in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts`\n    30→  - [x]The method takes `projectDir` so providers can inspect project files (e.g., Cargo.toml for Bevy detection)\n    31→  - [x]Return type is `string` — a Dockerfile snippet (RUN/ENV lines) for that stack's tooling\n    32→\n    33→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 3): Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on `NodejsProvider` in `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts`\n    34→  - [x]Install Node.js 20 LTS via nodesource\n    35→  - [x]Install Semgrep via pipx\n    36→  - [x]Install showboat and claude-code via npm\n    37→  - [x]Match current `Dockerfile.verify` functionality\n    38→\n    39→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 4): Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on `PythonProvider` in `src/lib/stacks/python.ts`\n    40→  - [x]Install python3-pip, python3-venv\n    41→  - [x]Install coverage, pytest\n    42→  - [x]Install Semgrep via pipx\n    43→\n    44→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 1, 2, 5): Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on `RustProvider` in `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts`\n    45→  - [x]Install Rust toolchain via rustup (`curl ... | sh -s -- -y --default-toolchain stable`)\n    46→  - [x]Install clippy (`rustup component add clippy`)\n    47→  - [x]Install cargo-tarpaulin (`cargo install cargo-tarpaulin`)\n    48→  - [x]Set `ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:$PATH\"` for PATH inheritance\n    49→  - [x]Detect Bevy: read Cargo.toml at `projectDir`, check `[dependencies]` section for `bevy`\n    50→  - [x]If Bevy detected, add system libs: `libudev-dev libasound2-dev libwayland-dev libxkbcommon-dev libfontconfig1-dev libx11-dev`\n    51→  - [x]If Bevy NOT detected, skip system libs\n    52→  - [x]Use existing `readTextSafe` and `getCargoDepsSection`/`hasCargoDep` utils from `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts`\n    53→\n    54→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 1, 3, 4, 5, 7): Create `src/modules/verify/dockerfile-generator.ts` with `generateVerifyDockerfile()`\n    55→  - [x]Function signature: `generateVerifyDockerfile(projectDir: string): string`\n    56→  - [x]Call `detectStacks(projectDir)` to get all detected stacks\n    57→  - [x]Build Dockerfile from sections:\n    58→    1. Base image: `FROM ubuntu:22.04`\n    59→    2. Common tools: `curl jq git python3 pipx`\n    60→    3. Semgrep: `pipx install semgrep && pipx ensurepath`\n    61→    4. Per-stack sections: iterate detections, call `getStackProvider(detection.stack).getVerifyDockerfileSection(projectDir)`\n    62→    5. OTLP env vars: `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`, etc.\n    63→    6. `WORKDIR /workspace`\n    64→  - [x]Return the complete Dockerfile as a string\n    65→  - [x]Keep file under 100 lines\n    66→\n    67→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 1, 3, 7, 10): Update `src/modules/verify/env.ts` to use `generateVerifyDockerfile()`\n    68→  - [x]Replace `buildSimpleImage()` calls for `rust` and `generic` with new generator path\n    69→  - [x]Replace `buildNodeImage()` Dockerfile resolution with generated Dockerfile\n    70→  - [x]Replace `buildPythonImage()` Dockerfile resolution with generated Dockerfile\n    71→  - [x]Write generated Dockerfile to build context instead of copying from templates\n    72→  - [x]Remove or deprecate `resolveDockerfileTemplate()` and `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` constant\n    73→  - [x]Goal: reduce `env.ts` line count (currently 313) or at minimum keep it flat\n    74→\n    75→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 1, 2, 5, 7): Add unit tests for the generator\n    76→  - [x]Test: Rust project with bevy -> Dockerfile contains Bevy system libs\n    77→  - [x]Test: Rust project without bevy -> Dockerfile does NOT contain Bevy system libs\n    78→  - [x]Test: Rust Dockerfile contains `ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:$PATH\"`\n    79→  - [x]Test: Node.js project -> Dockerfile contains Node.js 20, npm, showboat\n    80→  - [x]Test: Python project -> Dockerfile contains python3-pip, coverage\n    81→  - [x]Test: Multi-stack project -> Dockerfile contains sections for all stacks\n    82→  - [x]Test: Generic/plugin project -> Dockerfile contains only base + common tools\n    83→\n    84→- [x] Task 8 (AC: 6, 8): Add unit tests for each provider's `getVerifyDockerfileSection()`\n    85→  - [x]Test: `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` with Bevy project\n    86→  - [x]Test: `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` without Bevy\n    87→  - [x]Test: `NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` returns Node.js section\n    88→  - [x]Test: `PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` returns Python section\n    89→\n    90→- [x] Task 9 (AC: 8): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    91→- [x] Task 10 (AC: 9): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    92→- [x] Task 11 (AC: 10): Verify line counts — `env.ts` should not grow, new `dockerfile-generator.ts` under 100 lines\n    93→\n    94→## Dev Notes\n    95→\n    96→### Architecture Compliance\n    97→\n    98→- **Decision 10 (Stack-Aware Provisioning):** This story implements the core of Decision 10. The architecture mandates that verification Dockerfiles are GENERATED per-project from stack provider methods, not selected from static templates. The current static template approach (`Dockerfile.verify`, `Dockerfile.verify.rust`, `Dockerfile.verify.generic`) is replaced by dynamic generation.\n    99→- **NFR1 (300-line limit):** `env.ts` is already at 313 lines (over limit). This story should REDUCE it by extracting the generator to `dockerfile-generator.ts`. Do NOT add lines to `env.ts`.\n   100→- **NFR5 (Commands <100 lines):** `verify-env.ts` is at 157 lines — do not touch it beyond import changes if needed.\n   101→\n   102→### Implementation Guidance\n   103→\n   104→#### Current State Assessment\n   105→\n   106→1. **`src/modules/verify/env.ts`** (313 lines) — Contains `buildVerifyImage()`, `buildNodeImage()`, `buildPythonImage()`, `buildSimpleImage()`, `buildPluginImage()`, and `resolveDockerfileTemplate()`. These use STATIC templates from `templates/Dockerfile.verify*`. This story replaces the template selection with dynamic generation.\n   107→2. **Static templates exist:**\n   108→   - `templates/Dockerfile.verify` — Node.js verification (node:20-slim base, npm pack, install from tarball)\n   109→   - `templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust` — Rust verification (rust:1.82-slim base, semgrep, tarpaulin, Node.js)\n   110→   - `templates/Dockerfile.verify.generic` — Generic/plugin verification\n   111→3. **`StackProvider` interface** (`src/lib/stacks/types.ts`, 96 lines) — Has `getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` for app Dockerfiles, but NO verify-specific method.\n   112→4. **`RustProvider`** (239 lines) has `hasCargoDep()` utility already importable from `utils.ts` — use it for Bevy detection.\n   113→5. **`detectStacks()`** returns `StackDetection[]` with `{ stack: StackName, dir: string }` — use this for multi-stack support.\n   114→\n   115→#### What to add\n   116→\n   117→**`src/lib/stacks/types.ts`** — Add to `StackProvider` interface:\n   118→```typescript\n   119→/** Return Dockerfile snippet for verification environment tooling. */\n   120→getVerifyDockerfileSection(projectDir: string): string;\n   121→```\n   122→\n   123→**`src/lib/stacks/rust.ts`** — New method on `RustProvider`:\n   124→- Detect Bevy via `hasCargoDep(getCargoDepsSection(cargoContent), 'bevy')`\n   125→- Return Dockerfile lines for: rustup install, clippy, tarpaulin, PATH env, and conditional Bevy system libs\n   126→- Reuse existing `readTextSafe`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` from `utils.ts`\n   127→\n   128→**`src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts`** — New method on `NodejsProvider`:\n   129→- Return Dockerfile lines for: Node.js 20 via nodesource, npm global tools (showboat, claude-code)\n   130→\n   131→**`src/lib/stacks/python.ts`** — New method on `PythonProvider`:\n   132→- Return Dockerfile lines for: pip, venv, coverage, pytest\n   133→\n   134→**`src/modules/verify/dockerfile-generator.ts`** — NEW file:\n   135→- `generateVerifyDockerfile(projectDir: string): string`\n   136→- Calls `detectStacks()`, iterates providers, assembles Dockerfile\n   137→- Base image: `ubuntu:22.04` (common base for multi-stack)\n   138→- Common layer: curl, jq, git, python3, pipx, semgrep\n   139→- Per-stack sections from providers\n   140→- OTLP env vars\n   141→- Target: under 100 lines\n   142→\n   143→**`src/modules/verify/env.ts`** — Modify build functions:\n   144→- Replace template-based builds with `generateVerifyDockerfile()` calls\n   145→- Write generated Dockerfile to build context as a string (use `writeFileSync`)\n   146→- Remove `resolveDockerfileTemplate()` and `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` (dead code)\n   147→- Goal: reduce line count from 313\n   148→\n   149→#### What NOT to do\n   150→\n   151→- Do NOT delete the static template files yet — they may be used by older installed versions. Mark them as deprecated in comments.\n   152→- Do NOT change the `buildVerifyImage()` public API — it's called from `verify-env.ts` command.\n   153→- Do NOT change `detectProjectType()` — it's used for build strategy selection (npm pack vs simple build).\n   154→- Do NOT add Bevy detection as a separate function in env.ts — it belongs in `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()`.\n   155→- Do NOT hardcode Rust version — use `stable` toolchain via rustup, not a pinned version.\n   156→\n   157→#### Important: Node.js verify path\n   158→\n   159→The current `buildNodeImage()` uses `npm pack` to create a tarball, then builds from `Dockerfile.verify` which COPYs and installs the tarball. The generated Dockerfile approach needs to preserve this `npm pack` + `COPY tarball` + `npm install -g` flow for Node.js projects. The `NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` provides the NODE TOOLING section, but the tarball install logic stays in `buildNodeImage()` which writes additional Dockerfile lines into the build context.\n   160→\n   161→Consider: `generateVerifyDockerfile()` returns the BASE + TOOLING portion. Build-specific steps (tarball copy, project mount) are appended by the build function in `env.ts`.\n   162→\n   163→### Testing Guidance\n   164→\n   165→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   166→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'`\n   167→- Create new test file: `src/modules/verify/__tests__/dockerfile-generator.test.ts`\n   168→- Extend existing: `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/` for provider method tests\n   169→- Mock `detectStacks()` to return controlled stack detections\n   170→- Mock filesystem reads (`readTextSafe`) for Bevy detection tests\n   171→- Existing test patterns: see `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts` for env.ts mocking approach\n   172→\n   173→### Previous Story Intelligence (14-4)\n   174→\n   175→- Story 14-4 added `--observability-backend` (victoria/elk/none) support. `docker-setup.ts` ended at exactly 300 lines. `formatters.ts` grew by 23 lines (574 to 597).\n   176→- The 300-line limit was strictly enforced. Files at the limit required extraction or minimal changes.\n   177→- `env.ts` at 313 lines is ALREADY over the limit — this story should bring it down or at minimum not increase it.\n   178→- Test patterns: Vitest with `vi.mock()` for module mocking, `vi.fn()` for function stubs.\n   179→- Build verification: `npm run build` must succeed. `npm test` must pass all ~3683 vitest tests.\n   180→\n   181→### Key Observations About Existing Code\n   182→\n   183→1. **`buildSimpleImage()`** in `env.ts` calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, variant)` which looks up `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` map and finds the file in `templates/`. This is the function to replace.\n   184→2. **`buildNodeImage()`** calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir)` (no variant) which finds `templates/Dockerfile.verify`. This needs the tarball-specific logic preserved.\n   185→3. **`buildPythonImage()`** also calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir)` — same base template as Node.\n   186→4. **`buildPluginImage()`** calls `resolveDockerfileTemplate(projectDir, 'generic')` — uses generic template.\n   187→5. **The `writeFileSync` import is NOT currently in `env.ts`** — you'll need to add it for writing generated Dockerfiles.\n   188→6. **`getStackProvider()` can return `undefined`** — handle the case where no provider is registered for a detected stack.\n   189→\n   190→### Project Structure Notes\n   191→\n   192→- `src/modules/verify/` — Verification module. New `dockerfile-generator.ts` goes here.\n   193→- `src/lib/stacks/` — Stack providers. Interface change in `types.ts`, implementation in each provider.\n   194→- `templates/` — Static templates. Will become deprecated but not deleted.\n   195→\n   196→### References\n   197→\n   198→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 465-503] — Decision 10: Stack-Aware Provisioning\n   199→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 385-399] — Story 14-5 epic definition\n   200→- [Source: src/modules/verify/env.ts] — Current verify env (313 lines) — main modification target\n   201→- [Source: src/lib/stacks/types.ts] — StackProvider interface (96 lines) — add method\n   202→- [Source: src/lib/stacks/rust.ts] — RustProvider (239 lines) — add getVerifyDockerfileSection\n   203→- [Source: src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts] — NodejsProvider (346 lines) — add getVerifyDockerfileSection\n   204→- [Source: src/lib/stacks/python.ts] — PythonProvider (280 lines) — add getVerifyDockerfileSection\n   205→- [Source: src/lib/stacks/utils.ts] — readTextSafe, getCargoDepsSection, hasCargoDep utilities\n   206→- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify.rust] — Current static Rust verify template (will be deprecated)\n   207→- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify] — Current static Node.js verify template (will be deprecated)\n   208→\n   209→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   210→## Verification Requirements\n   211→\n   212→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile.proof.md`)\n   213→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   214→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   215→\n   216→## Documentation Requirements\n   217→\n   218→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   219→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile.md`\n   220→\n   221→## Testing Requirements\n   222→\n   223→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   224→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   225→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   226→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   227→\n   228→## Dev Agent Record\n   229→\n   230→### Agent Model Used\n   231→\n   232→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   233→\n   234→### Debug Log References\n   235→\n   236→### Completion Notes List\n   237→\n   238→- All 11 tasks completed. 20 new tests added (8 provider tests + 12 generator tests), all 3712 tests passing.\n   239→- env.ts reduced from 313 to 304 lines (net -9). dockerfile-generator.ts is 63 lines (under 100 limit).\n   240→- Removed `resolveDockerfileTemplate()` and `DOCKERFILE_VARIANTS` dead code from env.ts.\n   241→- Updated 1 existing test in verify-env.test.ts (template resolution test replaced with generated Dockerfile test).\n   242→\n   243→### Change Log\n   244→\n   245→- 2026-03-25: Story created with 10 ACs (2 from epic, 8 derived from architecture Decision 10, existing code audit, multi-stack support, line-limit enforcement, and regression prevention). Full implementation guidance with file locations, line budgets, current-state assessment, Node.js tarball path notes, and anti-patterns. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n   246→- 2026-03-25: Implementation complete. All tasks done. Status set to review.\n   247→\n   248→### File List\n   249→\n   250→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Added `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` to `StackProvider` interface\n   251→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Implemented `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on NodejsProvider\n   252→- `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` — Implemented `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on PythonProvider\n   253→- `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts` — Implemented `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` on RustProvider (with Bevy detection)\n   254→- `src/modules/verify/dockerfile-generator.ts` — NEW: `generateVerifyDockerfile()` assembles Dockerfile from stack providers\n   255→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Replaced template-based builds with generated Dockerfiles, removed dead code\n   256→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/dockerfile-generator.test.ts` — NEW: 12 tests for generator\n   257→- `src/lib/stacks/__tests__/verify-dockerfile-section.test.ts` — NEW: 8 tests for provider methods\n   258→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-env.test.ts` — Updated: mocked generator, replaced obsolete template test\n   259→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012E2YPwx3Sod1tV3vRcBSTR","session_id":"748192fa-914a-4111-a5b7-9f2d46c0c1e7","uuid":"8565ea7a-b00f-4f7e-9fbc-b42e3ad60bbd","timestamp":"2026-03-27T08:23:10.793Z"}
